The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Decision on new venue on Saturday

Mumbai: The tour, programme and fixtures committee of the BCCI, headed by Shashank Manohar, will meet here on Saturday to decide on a new venue for the third and final India versus Sri Lanka Test following the inability expressed by the Uttar Pradesh Cricket Association (UPCA) in hosting it at Kanpurs Green Park. 

[This confirms a report in The Telegraph saying the Test could be shifted from Kanpur.] 

The UPCA has expressed its inability to conduct the match in Kanpur (from December 18-22). A decision on the new venue will be taken at Saturdaysmeeting, BCCIs executive secretary-in-charge Ratnakar Shetty said on Wednesday. The first Test of the series starts in Chennai on Friday, while the second Test is scheduled in Delhi from December 10. 

The committee is also likely to discuss the venues of the two warm-up games featuring England ahead of their three-Test series in February-March next year. 

 (PTI) 




